# Database Schema Master Index

As requested, I have created a comprehensive, modular database reference for SmartLab V6. This is organized by functional domains to ensure clarity and ease of access.

## Modules

### 1. [Core & Organization](db_core.md)
- Organizations & Plants
- User Profiles & Teams
- HR: Employees, Attendance, Shifts

### 2. [Production & MES](db_production.md)
- Production Batches & Lines
- Products & History
- Intermediates & Ingredients
- Equipments

### 3. [Laboratory & LIMS](db_lab.md)
- Samples & Types
- Lab Analysis & QA Parameters
- Product Specifications
- Microbiology: Results, Sessions, Media, Incubators

### 4. [Inventory & Supply Chain](db_inventory.md)
- Raw Materials & Packaging
- Reagents
- Suppliers

### 5. [Quality & Compliance](db_quality.md)
- QMS: Non-Conformities & CAPA
- Audit: Checklists & Findings
- HACCP: Hazards & PRP
- Sanitation: CIP Programs & Executions

### 6. [Insights & Auditing](db_audit.md)
- AI Insights
- Activity & System Logs
- Traceability Chain
- Training Records
- Compliance Reports (Generated Reports)
- SPC Alerts

---
> [!NOTE]
> These documents reflect the current schema in the `public` schema. Use these as the source of truth for all table and column names during implementation.
